01:10:07.358 --> 01:10:09.604
would have appeared in the past.

01:10:09.604 --> 01:10:12.576
So in some ways, lol and hahaha

01:10:12.576 --> 01:10:14.295
are just like punctuation.

01:10:14.295 --> 01:10:16.059
'Cause you don't put a period at the end,

01:10:16.059 --> 01:10:18.335
but you put haha at the
end or lol at the end.

01:10:18.335 --> 01:10:21.330
And it functions a bit like punctuation.

01:10:21.330 --> 01:10:25.881
So you can ask, computationally,
where does it appear?

01:10:25.881 --> 01:10:27.321
You could ask, I guess,

01:10:27.321 --> 01:10:30.131
what sorts of verbs does it appear after?

01:10:30.131 --> 01:10:32.824
You can ask questions like that.

01:10:32.824 --> 01:10:34.751
- Actually, I found something similar

01:10:34.751 --> 01:10:36.005
in my Tinder biography thing,

01:10:36.005 --> 01:10:38.954
I found that people used
emojis in place of a period.

01:10:38.954 --> 01:10:39.787
- Thank you.

01:10:39.787 --> 01:10:41.287
- Okay, thank you.

01:10:44.906 --> 01:10:48.073
- Thank you, this was quite wonderful.

01:10:49.434 --> 01:10:52.851
So, I'm thinking about intimacy, and what

01:10:54.055 --> 01:10:57.747
- Can you talk louder
and get the mic closer?

01:10:57.747 --> 01:11:00.301
- Thinking about intimacy.

01:11:00.301 --> 01:11:03.668
So I'm a therapist as
well as other things,

01:11:03.668 --> 01:11:05.618
and so I think a lot about that.

01:11:05.618 --> 01:11:08.591
And it's a theme in
what you were describing

01:11:08.591 --> 01:11:11.841
that is intriguingly deep and complex,

01:11:11.841 --> 01:11:14.326
about what represents intimacy.

01:11:14.326 --> 01:11:16.137
And as I was standing, waiting,

01:11:16.137 --> 01:11:18.088
I was reminded of Marshall McLuhan's

01:11:18.088 --> 01:11:20.784
cool and warm media, years ago.

01:11:20.784 --> 01:11:21.791
- What was the last thing you said?

01:11:21.791 --> 01:11:24.531
- Marshall McLuhan's cool
media and warm media.

01:11:24.531 --> 01:11:25.622
- Oh yes yes yes.

01:11:25.622 --> 01:11:28.385
- And these new technological ones

01:11:28.385 --> 01:11:31.009
seem to be cooler media.

01:11:31.009 --> 01:11:34.260
Not necessarily less intimate, different.

01:11:34.260 --> 01:11:37.766
So if we choose to be more available,

01:11:37.766 --> 01:11:40.529
which means texting, what does that mean?

01:11:40.529 --> 01:11:42.758
Does that mean I'm being more
available or less available?

01:11:42.758 --> 01:11:45.754
If I choose to do a phone
call because I can talk now

01:11:45.754 --> 01:11:48.285
but I can't do Facetime
because there's other stuff,

01:11:48.285 --> 01:11:50.746
is that being more
intimate or less intimate?

01:11:50.746 --> 01:11:52.487
And there's so much room,

01:11:52.487 --> 01:11:54.670
because there's less data,

01:11:54.670 --> 01:11:58.083
for misinterpretation on the one hand,

01:11:58.083 --> 01:12:01.334
or for, potentially for connection,

01:12:01.334 --> 01:12:03.447
because I'm more involved.

01:12:03.447 --> 01:12:05.096
Like the "hey."

01:12:05.096 --> 01:12:08.184
The recipient of hey has to spend

01:12:08.184 --> 01:12:10.970
much more time trying to understand

01:12:10.970 --> 01:12:13.548
who that person is and
what they're communicating

01:12:13.548 --> 01:12:16.009
that if it were going on in person.

01:12:16.009 --> 01:12:18.679
So for those of us of my generation

01:12:18.679 --> 01:12:22.882
it's interesting to think
about the subtleties of it.

01:12:22.882 --> 01:12:24.799
A, B, in doing therapy,

01:12:26.203 --> 01:12:29.291
I do have, as many of us probably have,

01:12:29.291 --> 01:12:31.938
the experience of someone talking to me

01:12:31.938 --> 01:12:33.494
about their relationship,

01:12:33.494 --> 01:12:35.769
and this terrible argument that they had

01:12:35.769 --> 01:12:37.418
with their boyfriend or girlfriend,

01:12:37.418 --> 01:12:39.183
where she said this and I said that,

01:12:39.183 --> 01:12:40.715
and I couldn't believe she said this

01:12:40.715 --> 01:12:41.923
and so I said that.

01:12:41.923 --> 01:12:43.594
And it takes me a while to get it,

01:12:43.594 --> 01:12:45.197
that this was all texting.

01:12:45.197 --> 01:12:46.845
- Yeah yeah yeah.

01:12:46.845 --> 01:12:48.178
- So, thank you.

01:12:49.841 --> 01:12:52.924
So any thoughts about the complexity

01:12:54.113 --> 01:12:56.530
of intimacy in the new world?

01:12:57.503 --> 01:12:59.848
- Yes yes, and all these observations

01:12:59.848 --> 01:13:02.217
are very significant and helpful.

01:13:02.217 --> 01:13:05.382
I guess the one thing I would say is that

01:13:05.382 --> 01:13:08.344
there's no one answer,
that it can be done,

01:13:08.344 --> 01:13:09.877
kind of like what I said,

01:13:09.877 --> 01:13:12.524
it can be more intimate and
it can be less intimate.

01:13:12.524 --> 01:13:14.381
Yeah, it's a cool medium,

01:13:14.381 --> 01:13:16.262
but Marshall McLuhan was
thinking of television.

01:13:16.262 --> 01:13:19.536
These things go right into your face,

01:13:19.536 --> 01:13:22.485
and in a way, what could
be more intimate than that?

01:13:22.485 --> 01:13:24.993
You could be in the
most personal situation,

01:13:24.993 --> 01:13:27.152
and here's this message right there.

01:13:27.152 --> 01:13:29.707
And it can be different
things for different people.

01:13:29.707 --> 01:13:31.216
So I think the crucial thing is

01:13:31.216 --> 01:13:33.886
to look at how it is being used

01:13:33.886 --> 01:13:35.767
by these people in this context,

01:13:35.767 --> 01:13:39.389
and ask, is it being more intimate

01:13:39.389 --> 01:13:41.433
or less intimate in this way.

01:13:41.433 --> 01:13:43.522
So some people maybe would find

01:13:43.522 --> 01:13:45.752
better communication if they occasionally

01:13:45.752 --> 01:13:48.259
backed off and texted or emailed.

01:13:48.259 --> 01:13:50.883
And other people have
to just put that aside

01:13:50.883 --> 01:13:53.112
and just talk to each other face to face.

01:13:53.112 --> 01:13:55.040
And maybe it's doing it differently

01:13:55.040 --> 01:13:56.479
than you did it before

01:13:56.479 --> 01:13:59.893
that might be some sort of a breakthrough.

01:13:59.893 --> 01:14:01.425
But I guess my strongest feeling is

01:14:01.425 --> 01:14:04.165
that there's no one way to look at it,

01:14:04.165 --> 01:14:05.999
and to be really cautious about

01:14:05.999 --> 01:14:07.927
how we respond to other people's

01:14:07.927 --> 01:14:09.877
uses of these media because

01:14:09.877 --> 01:14:12.547
their sense of it may
be different from ours.

01:14:12.547 --> 01:14:13.380
Thank you.

